Business Brief -- Horn  Hardart Co.:
   Large Shareholder Proposes
   Increase in Rights Offering
A Horn  Hardart spokesman said its board has yet to
discuss the proposal, which is contingent on certain
debtholders agreeing to an exchange offer. NAR, a joint
venture between the Quasha family and Cie. Financier
Richemont AG of Zug, Switzerland, holds six of 11 seats on
the Horn  Hardart board.
   Under the proposal, the rights offering to shareholders
will comprise $40 million of common stock and $20 million of
redeemable 9.5% cumulative preferred stock. NAR is committed
to purchase the units not subscribed for by other
shareholders.